<%- include('layout') %> <% title = "Mental Health | Women's Health Hub" %>

<div class="container py-5">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-8">
      <h1 class="mb-4">Women's Mental Health</h1>
      <p class="lead mb-4">
        Mental health is an essential component of overall wellness. Women face
        unique mental health challenges due to biological, hormonal, and
        societal factors. Learn about these challenges and effective strategies
        for maintaining and improving your mental well-being.
      </p>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">
            Women's Mental Health: Understanding the Landscape
          </h5>

          <p>
            Women experience certain mental health conditions at different rates
            than men and may have unique symptoms or triggers. Understanding
            these differences is key to better mental health care.
          </p>

          <div class="row mb-4">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <h6 class="mb-3">
                <i class="fas fa-chart-bar text-primary me-2"></i> Key
                Statistics
              </h6>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  Women are nearly twice as likely as men to be diagnosed with
                  depression
                </li>
                <li>
                  Anxiety disorders affect women at approximately twice the rate
                  of men
                </li>
                <li>Eating disorders are significantly more common in women</li>
                <li>PTSD affects twice as many women as men</li>
                <li>1 in 7 women experience postpartum depression</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <h6 class="mb-3">
                <i class="fas fa-brain text-primary me-2"></i> Contributing
                Factors
              </h6>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Biological:</strong> Hormonal fluctuations throughout
                  the menstrual cycle, pregnancy, and menopause
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Psychological:</strong> Tendency to internalize
                  stress, perfectionism
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Social:</strong> Gender-based violence, caregiving
                  responsibilities, workplace discrimination
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Economic:</strong> Income inequality, financial
                  insecurity
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-info">
            <i class="fas fa-info-circle me-2"></i>
            <strong>Did you know?</strong> Women's brain chemistry and hormonal
            influences can affect how they experience mental health conditions
            and respond to treatments. Research is increasingly focusing on
            gender-specific approaches to mental health care.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Common Mental Health Concerns for Women</h5>

          <div class="accordion" id="mentalHealthAccordion">
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingDepression">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseDepression"
                  aria-expanded="true"
                  aria-controls="collapseDepression"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-cloud-rain me-2 text-primary"></i> Depression
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseDepression"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse show"
                aria-labelledby="headingDepression"
                data-bs-parent="#mentalHealthAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-7">
                      <p>
                        Depression is more than just feeling sad. It's a
                        persistent feeling of sadness, loss of interest, and
                        impaired functioning that affects daily life.
                      </p>

                      <h6 class="mt-3">Women-Specific Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          Hormonal changes during puberty, before menstruation,
                          during and after pregnancy, and around menopause can
                          trigger or worsen depression
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          Women may experience depression differently, with more
                          symptoms like fatigue, irritability, sleep problems,
                          anxiety, and comfort eating
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          Social factors like relationship stress, work-life
                          balance challenges, and caregiving responsibilities
                          contribute to depression risk
                        </li>
                      </ul>

                      <h6 class="mt-3">Treatment Options:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          Psychotherapy (talk therapy) like cognitive-behavioral
                          therapy (CBT)
                        </li>
                        <li>Medication (antidepressants)</li>
                        <li>
                          Lifestyle changes (exercise, nutrition, sleep hygiene)
                        </li>
                        <li>Support groups</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-5">
                      <div class="alert alert-warning h-100">
                        <h6>
                          <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle me-2"></i>
                          Warning Signs:
                        </h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Persistent sadness or empty mood</li>
                          <li>Loss of interest in activities once enjoyed</li>
                          <li>Changes in appetite or weight</li>
                          <li>Sleep disturbances</li>
                          <li>Fatigue or energy loss</li>
                          <li>Feelings of worthlessness or guilt</li>
                          <li>Difficulty concentrating</li>
                          <li>Thoughts of death or suicide*</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="small mb-0">
                          *If you or someone you know is having thoughts of
                          suicide, call or text 988 to reach the Suicide and
                          Crisis Lifeline.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingAnxiety">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseAnxiety"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseAnxiety"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-bolt me-2 text-primary"></i> Anxiety
                  Disorders
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseAnxiety"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingAnxiety"
                data-bs-parent="#mentalHealthAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-7">
                      <p>
                        Anxiety disorders involve excessive worry, fear, or
                        nervousness that interferes with daily activities. They
                        include generalized anxiety disorder, panic disorder,
                        social anxiety, and specific phobias.
                      </p>

                      <h6 class="mt-3">Women-Specific Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          Fluctuations in estrogen and progesterone can
                          influence anxiety levels
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          Women's tendency to ruminate (repetitively focus on
                          negative thoughts) may contribute to higher anxiety
                          rates
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          Anxiety often co-occurs with depression in women
                        </li>
                      </ul>

                      <h6 class="mt-3">Treatment Options:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT)</li>
                        <li>Medication (SSRIs, SNRIs, benzodiazepines)</li>
                        <li>Mindfulness and meditation</li>
                        <li>Relaxation techniques</li>
                        <li>Regular physical activity</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-5">
                      <div class="card h-100">
                        <div class="card-body">
                          <h6 class="card-title">
                            Quick Anxiety Relief Techniques
                          </h6>
                          <ol class="mb-0">
                            <li>
                              <strong>5-4-3-2-1 Grounding:</strong> Identify 5
                              things you see, 4 things you feel, 3 things you
                              hear, 2 things you smell, and 1 thing you taste
                            </li>
                            <li>
                              <strong>Box Breathing:</strong> Inhale for 4
                              counts, hold for 4, exhale for 4, hold for 4
                            </li>
                            <li>
                              <strong>Progressive Muscle Relaxation:</strong>
                              Tense and then release each muscle group
                            </li>
                            <li>
                              <strong>Thought Challenging:</strong> Question
                              anxious thoughts by asking for evidence
                            </li>
                            <li>
                              <strong>Mindful Observation:</strong> Focus
                              intently on one object for 1 minute
                            </li>
                          </ol>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingReproductive">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseReproductive"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseReproductive"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-venus me-2 text-primary"></i>
                  Reproductive-Related Mental Health
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseReproductive"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingReproductive"
                data-bs-parent="#mentalHealthAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    Women's reproductive events can significantly impact mental
                    health, requiring specific awareness and interventions.
                  </p>

                  <div class="table-responsive mb-3">
                    <table class="table table-bordered">
                      <thead class="table-light">
                        <tr>
                          <th>Condition</th>
                          <th>Description</th>
                          <th>Management Approaches</th>
                        </tr>
                      </thead>
                      <tbody>
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            <strong
                              >Premenstrual Dysphoric Disorder (PMDD)</strong
                            >
                          </td>
                          <td>
                            A severe form of PMS with significant mood symptoms
                            occurring before menstruation
                          </td>
                          <td>
                            <ul class="mb-0">
                              <li>SSRIs (continuous or luteal phase)</li>
                              <li>Hormonal treatments</li>
                              <li>Lifestyle modifications</li>
                              <li>Stress management techniques</li>
                            </ul>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td><strong>Perinatal Depression</strong></td>
                          <td>
                            Depression during pregnancy or within the first year
                            after birth
                          </td>
                          <td>
                            <ul class="mb-0">
                              <li>Therapy (IPT, CBT)</li>
                              <li>Support groups</li>
                              <li>Carefully selected medications</li>
                              <li>Social support mobilization</li>
                            </ul>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td><strong>Postpartum Anxiety</strong></td>
                          <td>
                            Excessive worry, racing thoughts, and physical
                            symptoms after childbirth
                          </td>
                          <td>
                            <ul class="mb-0">
                              <li>CBT or other therapy</li>
                              <li>Mindfulness practices</li>
                              <li>Medication when appropriate</li>
                              <li>Sleep support</li>
                            </ul>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            <strong
                              >Perimenopause/Menopause-Related Mood
                              Changes</strong
                            >
                          </td>
                          <td>
                            Mood fluctuations during the transition to menopause
                          </td>
                          <td>
                            <ul class="mb-0">
                              <li>Hormone therapy (if appropriate)</li>
                              <li>Antidepressants</li>
                              <li>Lifestyle modifications</li>
                              <li>Stress reduction techniques</li>
                            </ul>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                      </tbody>
                    </table>
                  </div>

                  <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <i class="fas fa-info-circle me-2"></i>
                    <strong>Did you know?</strong> Tracking mood changes
                    alongside your menstrual cycle can help identify patterns
                    and inform treatment approaches for conditions like PMDD.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTrauma">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseTrauma"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseTrauma"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-heart-broken me-2 text-primary"></i> Trauma &
                  PTSD
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseTrauma"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingTrauma"
                data-bs-parent="#mentalHealthAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    Post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) develops in some
                    people after experiencing or witnessing a traumatic event.
                    Women are more likely than men to develop PTSD, partly due
                    to higher rates of sexual trauma and intimate partner
                    violence.
                  </p>

                  <h6 class="mt-3">Common Symptoms:</h6>
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <ul>
                        <li>Intrusive memories or flashbacks</li>
                        <li>Nightmares about the traumatic event</li>
                        <li>
                          Severe emotional distress or physical reactions to
                          reminders
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          Avoidance of trauma-related thoughts or feelings
                        </li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <ul>
                        <li>Negative thoughts about yourself or others</li>
                        <li>Feeling emotionally numb or detached</li>
                        <li>Being easily startled or frightened</li>
                        <li>Difficulty sleeping or concentrating</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>

                  <h6 class="mt-3">Effective Treatments:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <strong
                        >Trauma-focused cognitive behavioral therapy
                        (TF-CBT)</strong
                      >
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong
                        >Eye movement desensitization and reprocessing
                        (EMDR)</strong
                      >
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Prolonged exposure therapy</strong></li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Medication</strong> (SSRIs, prazosin for
                      nightmares)
                    </li>
                  </ul>

                  <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle me-2"></i>
                    <strong>Important:</strong> Recovery from trauma is
                    possible. Trauma-informed care recognizes the widespread
                    impact of trauma and paths to recovery, and seeks to
                    actively avoid re-traumatization.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingEating">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseEating"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseEating"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-utensils me-2 text-primary"></i> Eating
                  Disorders
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseEating"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingEating"
                data-bs-parent="#mentalHealthAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    Eating disorders are serious mental health conditions
                    characterized by disturbed eating behaviors and related
                    thoughts and emotions. They affect people of all genders but
                    are more commonly diagnosed in women.
                  </p>

                  <h6 class="mt-3">Common Types:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Anorexia Nervosa:</strong> Restriction of food
                      intake leading to significantly low body weight, intense
                      fear of gaining weight
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Bulimia Nervosa:</strong> Cycles of binge eating
                      followed by compensatory behaviors like purging or
                      excessive exercise
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Binge Eating Disorder:</strong> Recurrent episodes
                      of eating large amounts of food with a feeling of lack of
                      control
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong
                        >Other Specified Feeding or Eating Disorders
                        (OSFED):</strong
                      >
                      Eating disorders that don't meet the full criteria for
                      other disorders but are still serious
                    </li>
                  </ul>

                  <h6 class="mt-3">Warning Signs:</h6>
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <ul>
                        <li>Dramatic weight loss or gain</li>
                        <li>Preoccupation with weight, food, and dieting</li>
                        <li>Frequently skipping meals or refusing to eat</li>
                        <li>Evidence of binge eating or purging</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <ul>
                        <li>Excessive exercise regimen</li>
                        <li>Withdrawal from social activities</li>
                        <li>Expressing negative body image</li>
                        <li>Use of dietary supplements or laxatives</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>

                  <h6 class="mt-3">Treatment Approaches:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Medical stabilization (if needed)</li>
                    <li>Nutritional counseling and rehabilitation</li>
                    <li>Psychotherapy (CBT, DBT, family-based treatment)</li>
                    <li>Medication for co-occurring conditions</li>
                    <li>Support groups</li>
                  </ul>

                  <div class="alert alert-danger">
                    <i class="fas fa-exclamation-circle me-2"></i>
                    <strong>Urgent:</strong> Eating disorders have the highest
                    mortality rate of any mental illness. Early intervention is
                    critical. If you or someone you know is struggling with an
                    eating disorder, seek professional help immediately.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Building Mental Wellness</h5>

          <p>
            Mental health exists on a spectrum, and everyone can benefit from
            practices that support psychological well-being. Here are
            evidence-based strategies to build and maintain mental wellness:
          </p>

          <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-2 g-4 mb-4">
            <div class="col">
              <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                    <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                      <div
                        class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                        style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                      >
                        <i class="fas fa-walking fa-lg"></i>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <h6 class="card-title mb-0">Physical Activity</h6>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <p class="card-text">
                    Regular exercise reduces symptoms of depression and anxiety,
                    improves sleep, and boosts mood through the release of
                    endorphins. Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate activity
                    most days.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col">
              <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                    <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                      <div
                        class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                        style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                      >
                        <i class="fas fa-brain fa-lg"></i>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <h6 class="card-title mb-0">Mindfulness Practices</h6>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <p class="card-text">
                    Meditation, mindful breathing, and present-moment awareness
                    reduce stress, improve focus, and help manage negative
                    thoughts. Even 5-10 minutes daily can make a difference.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col">
              <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                    <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                      <div
                        class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                        style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                      >
                        <i class="fas fa-users fa-lg"></i>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <h6 class="card-title mb-0">Social Connection</h6>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <p class="card-text">
                    Maintaining meaningful relationships provides emotional
                    support, reduces isolation, and buffers against stress.
                    Prioritize quality over quantity in your social connections.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col">
              <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                    <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                      <div
                        class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                        style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                      >
                        <i class="fas fa-bed fa-lg"></i>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <h6 class="card-title mb-0">Sleep Hygiene</h6>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <p class="card-text">
                    Quality sleep is essential for emotional regulation and
                    cognitive function. Establish a consistent sleep schedule,
                    create a restful environment, and limit screen time before
                    bed.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col">
              <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                    <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                      <div
                        class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                        style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                      >
                        <i class="fas fa-apple-alt fa-lg"></i>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <h6 class="card-title mb-0">Nutrition</h6>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <p class="card-text">
                    Emerging research shows connections between diet and mental
                    health. Focus on balanced meals with adequate protein,
                    complex carbohydrates, healthy fats, and plenty of fruits
                    and vegetables.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col">
              <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                    <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                      <div
                        class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                        style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                      >
                        <i class="fas fa-heartbeat fa-lg"></i>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <h6 class="card-title mb-0">Self-Compassion</h6>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <p class="card-text">
                    Treating yourself with the same kindness you would offer a
                    good friend reduces anxiety and depression. Practice
                    self-compassion by acknowledging your struggles without
                    harsh self-judgment.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-success">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb me-2"></i> <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Even
            small changes can have a significant impact on mental well-being.
            Start with one area that feels most manageable and build from there.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">When and How to Seek Help</h5>

          <p>
            Many women hesitate to seek mental health support due to stigma,
            time constraints, or cost concerns. However, early intervention
            often leads to better outcomes.
          </p>

          <h6 class="mt-4">
            <i class="fas fa-clipboard-list text-primary me-2"></i> Signs It's
            Time to Seek Professional Help:
          </h6>
          <div class="row mb-4">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <ul>
                <li>Persistent feelings of sadness or anxiety</li>
                <li>Inability to function in daily life</li>
                <li>Significant changes in sleep or appetite</li>
                <li>Withdrawal from activities and relationships</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <ul>
                <li>Excessive worry or fear</li>
                <li>Mood swings that disrupt your life</li>
                <li>Thoughts of harming yourself or others</li>
                <li>Increasing use of substances to cope</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h6>
            <i class="fas fa-user-md text-primary me-2"></i> Types of Mental
            Health Providers:
          </h6>
          <div class="table-responsive mb-4">
            <table class="table table-hover">
              <thead class="table-light">
                <tr>
                  <th>Provider Type</th>
                  <th>Credentials</th>
                  <th>Services</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>Psychiatrist</td>
                  <td>MD or DO</td>
                  <td>Diagnosis, medication management, sometimes therapy</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Psychologist</td>
                  <td>PhD, PsyD, or EdD</td>
                  <td>Psychological testing, therapy, treatment planning</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Licensed Professional Counselor (LPC)</td>
                  <td>Master's degree, state license</td>
                  <td>Individual and group therapy, counseling</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Licensed Clinical Social Worker (LCSW)</td>
                  <td>Master's in Social Work, license</td>
                  <td>Therapy, case management, resource connection</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Psychiatric Nurse Practitioner</td>
